Step-1 how to use the mysql database in python django
DATABASES = {
    'default': {
        'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.mysql',
        'NAME': 'authentication',
        'USER': 'root',
        'PASSWORD': '',
        'HOST': 'localhost',  # Set to 'localhost' if the database is on the same machine
        'PORT': '3306',                # Default MySQL port
    }
}
use it in your settings.py to use the mysql database in python django

